microTasks.description:
Create the OpenClaw prompt as a const called 'taskGenerationPrompt'. Use template literals to build the exact prompt: '📋 TASK GENERATION for project: ${idea.title}
Architecture: ${idea.analysis?.architecture || 'Not specified'}
Features: ${idea.analysis?.features?.join(', ') || 'Not specified'}

Generate ALL tasks needed to build this project...' Include the complete JSON structure specification with name, description, department, estimatedMinutes, priority, phase, and dependencies fields. Specify minimum 50 tasks covering setup, frontend, API, database, auth, testing, security, deployment, documentation.

Create a helper function called formatTaskForTelegram that takes task object and project object as parameters. Build a template literal string with the exact format: '🎯 EXECUTE TASK: [{task.department}] {task.name}
Project: {project.name} at {project.path}
Description: {task.description}
Dependencies: {task.dependencies || 'none'}

Complete this task. Follow all WORK-RULES. Send notification when done.' Return this formatted string.
